name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
A peaceful and tranquil park in the west side.
Great place for a leisure walk to enjoy the nature and best of all- it is free. You could enjoy the fresh air in the morning and enjoy natural scenery. You should be able to see some chicken or rooster along the way too.
The route was well maintained and clean, with ample bins along the route.
A great healthy family destination to visit, with something for everyone in the family.
Strongly recommended!!!

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
Lovely, older park with a nice Playground, views of the old Quarry and other mixed amenities.

The WWII Memorial is a nice touch. Lots of stairs and a great hill to climb, but worth the walk!

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
Walking into Bukit Batok Nature Park is another different experience; by looking at the surrounding area, I never expected another hidden gem in the Bukit Batok area.

It was an abandoned site around 36hectare, redeveloped in 1988; this park has a quarry pool with a stunning view of the limestone hill. This is my favorite spot in this park; the surrounding is peaceful, and enjoying turtles swimming around inside the pool.

This park is also a resident place for many birds, chickens, and water lizards. Some native wild orchids are also spotted here, and it's part of NParks orchid conservation program.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Proper concrete-tile paths that minimise slips and do not get your shoes muddy. I love how the various paths meander within the hill, and are sloped to give a good exercise. The quarry is beautiful. The best path is the one that leads to the WW2 memorial. See the quarry first, then go to WW2 memorial. There is a long flight of stairs at the memorial but the end point has nothing there. Just treat it as good exercise. A pity the memorial plate is beyond reading due to damage from Sun.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Serene and tranquil nature reserve in Bukit Batok. Not many people on a PH morning. It’s an easy trail with proper shady pathways with no mud at all. Took almost 5km/1.5h to complete the trail (with some detours and photo breaks). Nice place for a midpoint break at the quarry, there was an uncle flutist when we went there on 1 May 2022 (like those wuxia playing their bamboo flute by the lake). Birds were singing along to the tune of his music. Beautiful gem of nature away from the city 🌳

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Great nature park to escape the city for a few hours. There are paved paths here but some trails are quiet steep so come prepared wearing comfortable clothes and shoes and bring plenty of water. There are quite a few joggers running around and other just enjoying their time in nature. I am enjoying with my family

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Good place for beginner. You can start frm the bottom of the slope followed by the steps/stairs, 2-3 sets is a good start. If it's too easy for you, bring in some weights with u (can be body vest weights, few bottles of 1.5L water bottle in your back pack).

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Bukit Batok Nature Park is a place where you can explore the beauty of nature . The air is so fresh in the morning. Sometimes you can spot some rare birds around. Once in a while there is an old man that play bamboo flute somewhere near the lake. The rhythm echo through the space is pleasing to the ear.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Small but historic park in Singapore, which holds a history of the area being a quarry and the lake that the mining left behind. It’s not converted into a beautiful nature park for light trekking, exercising, nature watching, and even had a small playground for children and toilets nearby for convenience. There are carparks accessible to this area as well. Worth a visit if you’re around the area 👍

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Fairly tough uphill walk, nice view of the quarry. Can venture further to nature reserve. Lots of wild animals to see and animal poo on the walkway. Cooling and shady even the weather is hot. Too bad it's short

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
Interesting place. Have yet to completely explored this nature park. Serene small Reservoir with birds chirping and nice backdrop of Lorong Sesuai.

Many people are here to exercise and enjoy the morning breeze. There's also a playground for kids to play while the parents can chill at the benches.

Do bring along mosquito patch or Jel. The mosquito here are commando trained.

My purpose today is to jog and cycle up to Lorong Sesuai. Only managed to jog up and explored the area, while cycling, I lack the strength and limited gears to pedal up. Will definitely try it out again next time.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Beautiful nature park with a stunning quarry and historic memorial. Highlight for me is the fresh air and wildlife sounds early in the morning. Worth a visit.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Take bus 178 alight busstop PPIA and climbed up the steep slope towards WWII Memorial Site(giant history book) also known as Meeting Point 3,shown on Park map. Is really tiring climbing up the so my suggestion is enter by another access point for example from Bukit Batok Ave6(Meeting Point 1). Meeting Point 2 is where the toilets and Water Cooler and Playground area. Whole park is easy for hiking but there are some need up stairs is good for exercise. Is a pity that I lost my way never get to go to Little Guilin,where the Park map shown Quarry Cliff.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: The memorial park really nothing much but the stairs which those "joggers" use it for training... the way from exit 2 go all the way straight in will come to  guilin- like of pond look better the the "little guilin" itself... worth the walk all the way there, maybe like 15mins or so...

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: A shady park, good to visit even on a sunny afternoon. Helmed by big trees, the park exudes a tranquil experience as you walk on the path heading towards the cliff or climb the stone steps up the hill towards the War Memorial. The fresh pine and woody scent of the greenery refreshes the mind and body. A great place to go for a walk or exercise at any time of the day.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Located besides a busy road, you may find squirrels, red jungle fowls, monkeys and lizards in this tranquil park. Do enjoy the symphony of cicadas and birds. Avoid Sunday afternoons when it usually gets crowded.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: A very interesting park, but all the mountain roads are very steep.  If you have a bad knee, it is not recommended to go here.  There are many wild birds in the park, especially many roosters.  There are two parking lots, it is recommended to go by car.  I have been to many parks in Singapore and this is really special and original ecologic

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Great nature park to escape the city for a few hours. There are paved paths here but some trails are quiet steep so come prepared wearing comfortable clothes and shoes and bring plenty of water. There are quite a few joggers running around and other just enjoying their time in nature.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Very lush and compact secondary forest in Bukit Batok. Doesn’t look like much from the main road but there is an abundance of flora and fauna, as well as a quarry. You will be amazed with what you can see in here. Quite a number of trails, including one that will lead to a WWII memorial. Highly recommended.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Small nature park. Simple climbing n jogging tracks. Beautiful lake-cliff view.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Just went for a light morning run at Bukit Batok Nature Reserve. The light rain was refreshing and the cool weather made it the perfect running conditions. Would recommend this route to anyone looking for a peaceful and enjoyable run/walk amidst nice greenery.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
09 Dec 2022: Cool leisurely walk through the forest...scenic routes, challenging slopes plus a couple of up and down the steps

14 Sep 2021: Nice family friendly park with playground, fitness corner, toilets and even water fountains. Some may find it a little hilly and the paths are laid with bricks.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Bukit Batok Nature Park is developed from an abandoned quarry. There are several hiking trails, wetland, WW II Memorial, Transmission Centre & carpark inside the park.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Nice and tranquil park. Internally link to the Bukit Batok World War II memorial site. You can find many types of wild animal here like komodo dragon, monkeys, kampong chicken, squirrel etc. Good place for kid to cycle scooter. Also for old people to exercise as the trail is rather flat.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
Bukit Batok Nature Park is a hidden gem in Singapore that offers visitors a peaceful escape from the hustle and bustle of city life. Here are some positive comments about this beautiful park:

Serene and tranquil: The park is well-maintained and offers a tranquil and serene atmosphere that is perfect for a relaxing stroll, jog or picnic.
Picturesque beauty: The park is filled with lush greenery, picturesque scenery, and a stunning lake that offers breathtaking views. It is a perfect spot for photography enthusiasts.
Diverse flora and fauna: The park boasts a diverse range of flora and fauna, making it an excellent place for nature lovers. Visitors can spot various species of birds, butterflies, and plants in their natural habitat.
Fitness-friendly: The park is perfect for fitness enthusiasts as it has several walking and jogging trails that offer a challenging yet enjoyable workout. The park is also equipped with fitness stations and outdoor gym equipment.
Family-friendly: The park is a great place for families to spend quality time together. Children can play in the playground, while parents can relax and enjoy the scenery.
Overall, Bukit Batok Nature Park is a hidden gem in Singapore that offers visitors a peaceful retreat from the busy city life. Whether you want to explore nature, get fit, or just relax, this park is an excellent place to do so.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Rare to see rooster roaming around here. Bring back memories when I was young leaving in Kampong Village. Now our young z  generations only see died frozen chicken in supermarket.  🤭. Nice place to walk . 🚶‍♀️

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
Lovely, older park with a nice Playground, views of the old Quarry and other mixed amenities.

The WWII Memorial is a nice touch. Lots of stairs and a great hill to climb, but worth the walk!

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Great tracks on undulating slopes for quiet  moments with nature and to explore your inner self . Natural beauty, laughter of birds and other living ,will whisper their thoughts of you . Just wonder to  realise  that magical moments.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
My first time here and I’m impressed. The park is not that big but there are enough pockets of private spaces in the form of elevations and spacious corners to accommodate different activities. The lush trees allows for a shady and peaceful walk.

Just the right amount of slopes and off-road terrain to do a quick morning walk and get your heart pumping.

The majestic view of the quarry just makes reaching the destination all the more rewarding.

I will bring my binoculars the next time to catch views or any bird or wildlife in the trees or bushes!

Worth a visit! Go check it out!

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
Awesome Nature Park in Bukit Batok area.
There is a main running/walking track that is around 600m long which leads to a scenic lake with a great view of the cliffs.
There are also secondary trails which loop inside the park. These are recommended as they are very atmospheric and you can feel immersed in nature.
Another highlight of the park is the Japanese War Memorial which is located at the top of the cliff area.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Good place to go for a morning jog! Very well maintained and also if you're lucky,you can get to see a Malayan Colugo or the flying lemer resting on lower part of the trees camouflaged like a tree bump! What a fascinating animal! 😁

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
A nice calming park. Good for a 2 hr walk to take the edge out of city living.
There are uphills and staircases that leads up to the quarry and war memorial. Paved walkways make ls it easy.
The memorial is not really much. So u don’t have to try too hard to get there if the walk gets difficult for u.

Quarry place is calm and peaceful.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
I take this BBNK as my 2nd home. I was there when my son learning to walk in 34 yrs ago and the gardening workers was just started to planted more flowers on both side of the track.
It's precious that, Singapore well maintain the N Park n clean it for us  those who love the Natura n the Blue Sky. Here I shall say very thank you to our govn.

I use to regularly go there to play Taiji.
Before C19 it was not that crowded, aft the C19, every one had waken up n realise that health is very important,  so this park become more n more crowded in the early morning n evening every day.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: A shaded family-friendly trail with hills to climb, beautiful trees and the quarry was a fitting resting spot to have a snack and take photos before climbing up to see the WW2 memorial. Appreciate all the shade under the hot sun!

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Nice park for a short hikes. Sometimes at the quarry there is an old man playing on his flute which blends beautifully with the sounds of nature (birds chirping).

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Beautiful nature park with a stunning quarry and historic memorial. Highlight for me is the fresh air and wildlife sounds early in the morning. Worth a visit.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Well its one of many parks in singapore except this one comes equipped with a quarry view. Nice and challenging slopes for hiking and playground for kiddos.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
A nature lover's paradise. Walk, stroll ride a bicycle. The view is awesome along the nature trail. One sees so many birds, tortoises etc. An old stone querry also exists - a grim reminder how nature can be damaged.
Ps. It is open day night

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Xiao Guilin is what this place is known for. Nice hiking place to enjoy nature. Beaming with nature & wildlife. Lookout for birds, monkeys, squirrels, chickens, insects, fishes & even wild boars! Recommended place to go for nature lovers.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Small but lovely park to take a walk. The main attraction has to be the breathtaking quarry that's become a small but apparently deep lake. A wonderful place to find some peace and tranquility from the hustle and bustle of the day.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Just a fantastic natural atmosphere!! Green, water, Natural walking Tracks, nice rest areas. Another lovely relaxing jewel in the busy Singapore!! Just minutes away from Bukit Timah road but not as busy as you would expect it. Give yourself an hour and you will replenished!!

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
A peaceful and tranquil park in the west side.
Great place for a leisure walk to enjoy the nature and best of all- it is free.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: The place is peaceful and very calm when it comes to the ambiance. The pathway is clean and the reserve is so clean and does not have an garbage on its trail, kudos to that. Make sure that you follow the road till the end to find a small lake with a cliff. The lake has fishes and turtles in it. If you find any monkeys here please do not feed them as it serves as a particular purpose. Over all a well maintained reserve.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: This is a big nature park with alot of good clean air and  without the usual hot temperature associate with the outside busy bustling with cars and moving people here and there on the roadsides. It is comfortable to exercise in this area, doing jogging, fast running or slow pacing to each one suiting each own desire. Given a chance one may spots a wild boar coming out from the thick bushes out of nowhere suddendly. Quite an experience to have it happening right in front of you. But stay calm and walk away slowly, do not be frightened and running away because the animal will chase after you like what an angry dog will be doing. So enjoy yourself if you got a chance to come here.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Only managed to jog up and explored the area, while cycling, I lack the strength and limited gears to pedal up. Will definitely try it out again next time.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Calm and relaxing. Very short stroll that has a nice view of the quarry lake. We spotted a few critters along the way. Beautiful nature walk.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Nice park. Its internally link to the Bukit Batok World War II memorial site. You can also find many types of wild animal here like komodo dragon, kampong chicken, squirrel etc. Good place for kid to do cycle scooter.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Tranquil and scenic. Apart from a man made lake in the middle of the park, there are other more hidden scenic spots around the park. Good for hiking, walking, jogging, running and paktor-ing:)

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: The best nature reserve which I have ever visited and man it's so clean and pollution free. There is greenery all around and this makes your mind at peace. The sign boards are apt and clear for people who are new to this place. Make sure to go till the end of the pathway to find a serene lake and a small cliff which has tower on its top.

review_text: It is a Zen garden where you can meditate for hours and improve your mental health. I took my flute with me and it was a mesmerizing experience when it echoed. ⚡

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: The place was so beautiful 😍. Peace of mind. 😊 very nice Nature park & peaceful

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Beautiful walk with something to offer for everyone - steep slopes, stairs, beautiful views, sit-outs, playgrounds and meeting points perfect for groups looking to get a good walking workout!

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Although it's not a very long walk but there are quite a number of steep slopes. You can get quite a good workout.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Very peaceful place best place to enjoy with family. View are amazing picture perfect place must visit.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: We had a nice walk on a Saturday morning, there are cobble-stone-like pathways (just read the Wizard of Oz the night before), a former quarry and a lake... It's a nice park.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: What do you think you will be able to find here? Greenery obviously. What I like about Bukit Batok Nature Park is that there's the jungle walking part and the road path and some playground to try out. There's also the stone walking path which really hurts for me when I walk on it without any shoes or socks. So yes, its fun to go and hang out. Even at 10am,there is enough shade to hide under.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Small quiet park with a mix of (steep) walking trail and tarmac road access. No restriction on cycling or EV bikes/scooters. Might not be safe for late night/Early morning joggers. Toilets and water coolers facilities available

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
A nice place to bring your folks for a walk or a trekking "date" activities you can do for free in Singapore and get some exercise.

Do take note of falling branches and there are wild animals like monkeys, rooster, birds, squirrels turtle and fishes. (Haven't seen any snakes)

Do not bring plastic bags or eat during trekking it is best to find a sheltered spot to do so unless you want to be ransacked by animals or encounter daylight robbery by them. 😂

There are signages that I find hilarious so I usually spot them.

It should take about 45mins to an hour to complete trekking do bring a water bottle with you and stay hydrated.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: It is a very well path and shaded park and have a beautiful quarry. It can be rather quiet in the noon but I always love the serenity and the beauty of this ...

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Singapore have like that place ? I never think. More than 1000 times roaming nearer, but didn't look this nice and interested mountain. Anyone like natural resources can going through Bukit Gomback MRT station in Red line. And walk through. Very very interesting places. But don't forget no available shop. So before going bring drinking water. No take many more baggage. Because mountain. If you workout this very nice place.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: I cant stop going there🥰, love it so much the nature more relaxing and more at peace even you've company 🦎🐒😅

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
This park is much quieter as compared to the nearby Bukit Timah hill.
Surprisingly, this park is quite hilly and the paths are mostly laid with bricks. Hence, you have to be a little careful when walking on the paths. This park is a great park for bird watching enthusiasts.
We saw a number of white-crested laughing thrush. They even ‘performed’ a session for us!
There are also some pretty interesting looking trees.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: beautiful,  quiet, nor crowded. liked the white headed thrush...cute, handsome,  ....

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Very glad to have this park near by. A very good place for my regular walk. Lots of green and many interesting creation of God to be discovered and appreciate.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Good place to go for workouts or relaxing. Nice getaway from busy life to lush greenary with nature. Can easily accessible by bus, taxi or private vehicle. Views are amazing around the pond in the middle part of the area. Although it isn't a big area like other close by nature parks, it gives totally isolated feeling. Highly recommend for anyone to go there and enjoy the nature any day.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: We took a guided evening nature walk here with The Untamed Paths company. They were great and the location is amazing. Wildlife abounds, the paths are well kept and the seating is pleasant and widespread enough to work without being obtrusive.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Lovely, older park with a nice Playground, views of the old Quarry and other mixed amenities.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: It's very nice, Feeling like sitting in the lap of nature, greenery and beautiful views everywhere, a completely different place where you will really see a different feeling.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: Much to see here. There's a lake (or quarry?). A playground. Fitness corner. Toilets and drinking fountain. Interesting terrain. The hilly part of the park is paved with brick-like stones. So there's groves that will help drain water when it rains and aid in traction. But some parts can be a little steep, so go with decent footwear. There is also a World War II memorial.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park

There are public toilets/water cooler in the main plaza with rain shelter huts and outdoor exercise corner (2 monkey bars, dip bar, 2 pull up bars, 2 Australian pull up bars, etc). Park is connected to WW2 memorial and telecommunication installation.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
Good for a short hike - if we could call it that! It is meant for a walk rather than a proper hike and can be completed in about an hour or so. We actually did more than 2 rounds in our 2 hours there and kept bumping into the same people often :)

The up slope can be slightly demanding on the knees, but otherwise most of the terrain is flat. The best part for me was the quarry, it is stupendous and huge, not to mention that it is a great photo op too. Don't forget to get a peek at the quarry on the way up to the WW2 memorial. The other lovely part was the nice, open space in the center surrounded by trees. You could just sit by the periphery and watch people walking around.

Overall, BBNP is for the casual morning or evening walks and not for serious (even the not so serious) hikers.

review_text: This park is not to be confused with Little Guilin park near Bukit Gombak train station. It is located between the Old Jurong Road and Hillview Avenue along Bukit Batok Avenue 2 and 6 and the park area is much larger. You can visit the quarry, climb up the steps to the lookout point and World War 2 Memorial, watch birds and other wildlife.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text:
Usually visit this place during my off days, esp after sending my kid to school. Loved this place for the "forest like" kind of environment. Best time to visit before 8am when the air is fresher.

During my first few visits I was even expecting roaming wild boars so I watched my back as I strolled😳. Beware of falling branches as well esp after rain.

This nature park has the potential to extend further. There is a large chunk of greenery up north next to the heavy vehicle carpark and hopefully NParks can consider to extend the tracks up there.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: I loved the walk at the Bukit Batok park. There were some steep slopes and it is great for a morning walk. Went up and down the 121 steps at war memorial. It was awesome and I will go there agin sometime soon :) Also got to see some monkeys and squirrels.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: I love this park for its undulating trails, and the lovely quarry pond. Follow the sign board and head to Lor Sesuai to the WWII Memorial, and you can head down to Upper Bukit Timah, and then walk in to Bukit Timah Nature Reserve, and visit the Hindhede Quarry, before the final summit climb up the steep tarmac road. While coming down, go down via Rengas route on the right, take the Dairy Farm Loop, down the steep slope down on the right, out to Dairy Farm Car Park B. Then proceed along the path towards Car Park A, and enjoy your lunch at Rail Mall. The Hill View MRT is just along the Upper Bukit Timah Road. Have fun.

name: Bukit Batok Nature Park
review_text: A neighborhood park ideal for strolling, walking and running. A few densely tree lined trails zig zag across it. There is an old quarry pool in the center of the Park, surrounded by some facilities, including a public toilet, an outdoor fitness area, and a kids play ground in a sand pit. Friendly and relaxed ambiance.
